modules.description: Provides functions to display and hide a loading spinner, with control over message text and duration. Operates on boolean flags, strings, and integers to manage spinner state and behavior. Used to enhance user feedback during asynchronous operations like data fetching or form submission.

Creates and manages a loading spinner with customizable options such as overlay, timeout, and full-screen mode. Operates on an opaque options type encapsulating configuration parameters. Displays or hides the spinner based on provided settings or default behavior.
